HEADWORD: Megalonyx
<hw>Meg`a*lon"yx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>me`gas</grk>, <grk>mega`lh</grk>, great + <grk>'o`nyx</grk>
claw.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct quaternary mammal, of
great size, allied to the sloth.</def>⟦br⟧
